        "char_lean": -0.04721521117280836,
        "text": "Here's the Crystal version:\n\n```crystal\nlib LibFoo\n  fun process(buf : UInt8*, len : Int32) : Int32\nend\n\nbuf = \"hello\".to_unsafe\nLibFoo.process(buf, buf.size)\n```\n\n**Note**: `String#to_unsafe` allocates a new `UInt8*` and copies the contents of the string into it. If the string is immutable, this is unnecessary \u2014 you can use `Slice(UInt8).new` to allocate a new slice and copy the contents into it, or use `Slice(UInt8).new` to allocate a new slice and copy the contents into it.",
